{
    "plan": "1. Adjust the lengths of arrows F1 and F2 to be equal, ensuring that they visually represent |F1| = |F2|. 
2. Reposition the labels for forces F1 and F2 closer to their respective arrows for clarity. 
3. Add a clear label for the distance r, positioning it near the midpoint of the dashed line. 
4. Include the gravitational equation F = G(m1*m2)/r² as a note or label within the diagram for better understanding. 
5. Ensure the gravitational constant G is placed closer to the masses or forces to provide context. 
6. Reassess color choices for labels and arrows to ensure clarity and visual appeal.",
    "code": "fig, ax = plt.subplots()

# Define point masses
m1_x, m1_y = 1, 0
m2_x, m2_y = 3, 0

# Draw point masses
ax.plot(m1_x, m1_y, 'o', color='blue', markersize=20, label='m1')
ax.plot(m2_x, m2_y, 'o', color='green', markersize=20, label='m2')

# Draw forces with equal length
force_length = 0.5
ax.arrow(m1_x, m1_y, force_length, 0, head_width=0.1, head_length=0.2, fc='blue', ec='blue', label='F1')
ax.arrow(m2_x, m2_y, -force_length, 0, head_width=0.1, head_length=0.2, fc='green', ec='green', label='F2')

# Add distance line
ax.plot([m1_x, m2_x], [m1_y, m2_y], 'k--')

# Add labels
ax.text(1, -0.2, 'm1', fontsize=12, ha='center')
ax.text(3, -0.2, 'm2', fontsize=12, ha='center')
ax.text(2, 0.1, 'r', fontsize=12, ha='center')
ax.text(1.5, 0.5, 'F1', fontsize=12, color='blue', ha='center')
ax.text(2.5, 0.5, 'F2', fontsize=12, color='green', ha='center')
ax.text(2, -0.5, 'G ≈ 6.67428(67)×10−11 m³/(kg·s²)', fontsize=10, ha='center')
ax.text(2, -0.8, 'F = G(m1*m2)/r²', fontsize=10, ha='center')

# Set limits and labels
ax.set_xlim(0, 4)
ax.set_ylim(-1, 1)
ax.axis('off')

# Show legend
ax.legend()
"
}
